dden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104unv1665702768403.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/unv1665702768403.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/unv1665702768403.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"unv1665702768403\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Developing a Mobile App\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface's mobile solution is based on web technologies, so mobile development starts with creating a responsive web application that is tailored to the possibilities and limitations of mobile devices.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"unv1665702768403__context_w73ab1b5b1_w74ab1b5_w75ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"unv1665702768403__topic_d27983e1_d27984e1_d27985e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d27986e1_d27987e1_d27988e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oqd1665702768475.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oqd1665702768475.html\" title=\"Uniface takes away a great deal of the complexity of developing mobile apps for Android and iOS devices. However, there are some issues that you will need to manage and address yourself, especially before publishing your app to an app store.\">Requirements for Mobile App Development</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14195e1_d14196e1_d14197e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Model the application data and default behavior. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ffi1703160534674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffi1703160534674.html\" title=\"Modeling is an activity in which you create abstract development objects that can be reused by other objects during development. Modeled objects are used to represent the application data, centralize business logic, define default behavior, and enforce consistency.\">Modeling the Application</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14198e1_d14199e1_d14200e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d27989e1_d27990e1_d27991e1\">Construct one or more DSPs that use the mobile\n               app framework to define headers, footers, menus and navigation tools. For example,\n               you can define: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14201e1_d14202e1_d14203e1\">One DSP to serve as the main user interface\n                     of the app. It could contain two DSP container fields that are bound to the\n                     header and content of the Mobile App Layout. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wun1665702755914.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wun1665702755914.html\" title=\"Each mobile platform has its own user interface and interaction conventions, which affect the layout of a mobile application. The Mobile App Layout is a framework that maps HTML elements in a DSP layout to generic layout definitions.\">Mobile App Layout</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14204e1_d14205e1_d14206e1\">Other DSPs that contain the content to be\n                     displayed in the main DSP. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jix1665702767902.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jix1665702767902.html\" title=\"When developing a web application you need to follow the Uniface development paradigm of model, construct, build, test, and deploy. Web applications are stateless, so you need to consider how you will manage state, how to maximize performance, and protect security.\">Develop a Uniface Web Application</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14207e1_d14208e1_d14209e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d27992e1_d27993e1_d27994e1\">Program the application behavior using ProcScript\n               for server-side code, and JavaScript for client-side code. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">To address Uniface objects, use the Uniface JavaScript API. For more information,\n                  see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvf1665702667063.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvf1665702667063.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications.\">Scripting Application Behavior</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owl1665702532596.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" title=\"The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.\">APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a>. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d27995e1_d27996e1_d27997e1\">To address device-specific objects, use hybrid\n                  framework plug-in APIs.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14210e1_d14211e1_d14212e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create the icons and splash screens that are required on your target\n               platform.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14213e1_d14214e1_d14215e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d27998e1_d27999e1_d28000e1\">Use your preferred hybrid framework to package the mobile app. You can choose to:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14216e1_d14217e1_d14218e1\">Provide the URL of your web application to the hybrid wrapper. This is the simplest option, but it requires all resources to be downloaded from the server when the app is run.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14219e1_d14220e1_d14221e1\">Deploy the DSP runtime and static content (including CSS, icons and splash screens, JavaScript) to the framework so they can be packaged into the app. This ensures that these resources are available locally, providing better performance.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"unv1665702768403__p_d28001e1_d28002e1_d28003e1\">The specific instructions will vary, but the basic steps are typically to:</p>\n</div>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14222e1_d14223e1_d14224e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a project for your app in the hybrid framework.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14225e1_d14226e1_d14227e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure this project with information such as the application name, URL, target platforms, application page, and so on required to create the mobile app package.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14228e1_d14229e1_d14230e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Specify or install any hybrid framework plug-ins you will be using to access native device functionality.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14231e1_d14232e1_d14233e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you are including the Uniface JavaScript runtime (<span class=\"ph filepath\">common/uniface.js</span>) and static resources, copy them from the Uniface web folder to the framework web root. For example, depending on your application, you might copy the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">/css</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">/dspjs</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">/images</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">/fonts</span>, and <span class=\"ph filepath\">/images</span> folders.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"unv1665702768403__li_d14234e1_d14235e1_d14236e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Build the package using the framework commands.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532773\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532773\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Developing a Mobile App Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Developing a Mobile App Uniface's mobile solution is based on web technologies, so mobile development starts with creating a responsive web application that is tailored to the possibilities and limitations of mobile devices. For more information, see Requirements for Mobile App Development . Model the application data and default behavior. For more information, see Modeling the Application . Construct one or more DSPs that use the mobile app framework to define headers, footers, menus and navigation tools. For example, you can define: One DSP to serve as the main user interface of the app. It could contain two DSP container fields that are bound to the header and content of the Mobile App Layout. For more information, see Mobile App Layout . Other DSPs that contain the content to be displayed in the main DSP. For more information, see Develop a Uniface Web Application . Program the application behavior using ProcScript for server-side code, and JavaScript for client-side code. To address Uniface objects, use the Uniface JavaScript API. For more information, see Scripting Application Behavior and APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript . To address device-specific objects, use hybrid framework plug-in APIs. Create the icons and splash screens that are required on your target platform. Use your preferred hybrid framework to package the mobile app. You can choose to: Provide the URL of your web application to the hybrid wrapper. This is the simplest option, but it requires all resources to be downloaded from the server when the app is run. Deploy the DSP runtime and static content (including CSS, icons and splash screens, JavaScript) to the framework so they can be packaged into the app. This ensures that these resources are available locally, providing better performance. The specific instructions will vary, but the basic steps are typically to: Create a project for your app in the hybrid framework. Configure this project with information such as the application name, URL, target platforms, application page, and so on required to create the mobile app package. Specify or install any hybrid framework plug-ins you will be using to access native device functionality. If you are including the Uniface JavaScript runtime ( common/uniface.js ) and static resources, copy them from the Uniface web folder to the framework web root. For example, depending on your application, you might copy the /common , /css , /dspjs , /images , /fonts , and /images folders. Build the package using the framework commands. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}